                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="221874" author="adilger" created="Wed, 28 Feb 2018 00:51:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Implemented as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9771&quot; title=&quot;FLR1: Landing tickets for File Level Redundancy Phase 1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9771&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9771&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64899" author="jay" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2013 22:17:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;indeed. Things are a little easier than before since we have exclusive open. So let&apos;s define a command as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lfs raid1_make_it_raid1 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;options like lfs setstripe&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;existing_file&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to turn an existing file into a raid1 file, or add one more copy to a raid1 file. In this command, the following steps will be performed:&lt;br/&gt;
1. create a temp file with speicified stripe pattern or default policy;&lt;br/&gt;
2. open the existing file exclusively;&lt;br/&gt;
3. copy the file content to the temp file;&lt;br/&gt;
4. lfs raid1_merge&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this implementation of raid1_make_it_raid1 should have lower priority. The most important thing is still to finish the IO infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64879" author="adilger" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2013 19:42:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This task should also include the functionality to make a replica copy of an existing file.  I don&apos;t want the user tools to only do split/merge of a replicated file, but the user is required to write their own script to make a copy of the file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
